narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: A very good introduction to harmonic analysis.
I gained a general familiarity with the principles underlying the main ideas in harmonic analysis, which is a field with many applications relevant to my interests.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I wish there were notes or maybe selected readings from a textbook to more closely follow. But otherwise this was taught well.

The strengths were Dr. Coifman's true mastery of the material, as he is one of the people who established the field. Sometimes I would get a bit lost, but that is more my fault than a fault of the course.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Professor Coifman is a genius - I'd recommend any time you are able to learn from him.
